{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887268913,"sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b213384001wFt5Sy9220CDSz","messageID":"msg_d7b21273a001ZLlD5vTzHHjbRG","sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_959e14f9f1524b11ba99b1b4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: agent-runtime\n3: title: Agent Runtime API\n4: description: Agent Runtime API reference\n5: sidebar_position: 1\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Agent Runtime API\n9: \n10: The Agent Runtime API provides programmatic access to agent management and execution.\n11: \n12: ## Base URL\n13: \n14: ```\n15: http://localhost:8080/api/v1\n16: ```\n17: \n18: ## Authentication\n19: \n20: All API requests require an API key in the header:\n21: \n22: ```bash\n23: curl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" ...\n24: ```\n25: \n26: ## Endpoints\n27: \n28: ### Create Agent\n29: \n30: Create a new agent.\n31: \n32: ```http\n33: POST /agents\n34: ```\n35: \n36: **Request Body:**\n37: \n38: ```json\n39: {\n40:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n41:   \"description\": \"A helpful assistant\",\n42:   \"model\": \"gpt-4\",\n43:   \"instructions\": \"You are a helpful assistant.\",\n44:   \"tools\": [\"code-interpreter\", \"web-search\"],\n45:   \"metadata\": {\n46:     \"team\": \"engineering\"\n47:   }\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: **Response:**\n52: \n53: ```json\n54: {\n55:   \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n56:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n57:   \"status\": \"active\",\n58:   \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n59: }\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Get Agent\n63: \n64: Retrieve agent details.\n65: \n66: ```http\n67: GET /agents/{agent_id}\n68: ```\n69: \n70: **Response:**\n71: \n72: ```json\n73: {\n74:   \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n75:   \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n76:   \"description\": \"A helpful assistant\",\n77:   \"model\": \"gpt-4\",\n78:   \"status\": \"active\",\n79:   \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n80:   \"updated_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n81: }\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ### List Agents\n85: \n86: List all agents.\n87: \n88: ```http\n89: GET /agents\n90: ```\n91: \n92: **Query Parameters:**\n93: \n94: | Parameter | Type | Description |\n95: |-----------|------|-------------|\n96: | `limit` | int | Max results (default: 20) |\n97: | `offset` | int | Pagination offset |\n98: | `status` | string | Filter by status |\n99: \n100: **Response:**\n101: \n102: ```json\n103: {\n104:   \"agents\": [\n105:     {\n106:       \"id\": \"agent_abc123\",\n107:       \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n108:       \"status\": \"active\"\n109:     }\n110:   ],\n111:   \"total\": 1\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Update Agent\n116: \n117: Update an existing agent.\n118: \n119: ```http\n120: PATCH /agents/{agent_id}\n121: ```\n122: \n123: **Request Body:**\n124: \n125: ```json\n126: {\n127:   \"instructions\": \"You are a helpful coding assistant.\",\n128:   \"tools\": [\"code-interpreter\"]\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Delete Agent\n133: \n134: Delete an agent.\n135: \n136: ```http\n137: DELETE /agents/{agent_id}\n138: ```\n139: \n140: **Response:** `204 No Content`\n141: \n142: ### Invoke Agent\n143: \n144: Invoke an agent to process a request.\n145: \n146: ```http\n147: POST /agents/{agent_id}/invoke\n148: ```\n149: \n150: **Request Body:**\n151: \n152: ```json\n153: {\n154:   \"message\": \"Hello, how are you?\",\n155:   \"session_id\": \"session_abc123\",\n156:   \"stream\": false,\n157:   \"context\": {}\n158: }\n159: ```\n160: \n161: **Response:**\n162: \n163: ```json\n164: {\n165:   \"response\": \"I'm doing well, thank you!\",\n166:   \"session_id\": \"session_abc123\",\n167:   \"usage\": {\n168:     \"input_tokens\": 10,\n169:     \"output_tokens\": 15,\n170:     \"total_tokens\": 25\n171:   }\n172: }\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ### Stream Invoke\n176: \n177: Invoke an agent with streaming response.\n178: \n179: ```http\n180: POST /agents/{agent_id}/invoke\n181: ```\n182: \n183: **Request Body:**\n184: \n185: ```json\n186: {\n187:   \"message\": \"Write a story\",\n188:   \"stream\": true\n189: }\n190: ```\n191: \n192: **Response (Server-Sent Events):**\n193: \n194: ```stream\n195: data: {\"chunk\": \"Once\", \"done\": false}\n196: data: {\"chunk\": \" upon\", \"done\": false}\n197: data: {\"chunk\": \" a time\", \"done\": false}\n198: data: {\"done\": true}\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ## Types\n202: \n203: ### Agent\n204: \n205: ```typescript\n206: interface Agent {\n207:   id: string;\n208:   name: string;\n209:   description?: string;\n210:   model: string;\n211:   instructions: string;\n212:   tools: string[];\n213:   metadata: Record<string, string>;\n214:   status: 'active' | 'paused' | 'deleted';\n215:   created_at: string;\n216:   updated_at: string;\n217: }\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### InvocationRequest\n221: \n222: ```typescript\n223: interface InvocationRequest {\n224:   message: string;\n225:   session_id?: string;\n226:   stream?: boolean;\n227:   context?: Record<string, unknown>;\n228:   temperature?: number;\n229:   max_tokens?: number;\n230: }\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### InvocationResponse\n234: \n235: ```typescript\n236: interface InvocationResponse {\n237:   response: string;\n238:   session_id: string;\n239:   usage: {\n240:     input_tokens: number;\n241:     output_tokens: number;\n242:     total_tokens: number;\n243:   };\n244:   metadata?: Record<string, unknown>;\n245: }\n246: ```\n247: \n248: ## Error Codes\n249: \n250: | Code | Description |\n251: |------|-------------|\n252: | `400` | Bad Request |\n253: | `401` | Unauthorized |\n254: | `404` | Agent Not Found |\n255: | `429` | Rate Limited |\n256: | `500` | Internal Server Error |\n257: | `503` | Service Unavailable |\n258: \n259: ## Rate Limits\n260: \n261: - **Standard**: 60 requests/minute\n262: - **Pro**: 600 requests/minute\n263: - **Enterprise**: Custom\n264: \n265: ## SDK Examples\n266: \n267: ### Python\n268: \n269: ```python\n270: from agentcube import AgentRuntime\n271: \n272: client = AgentRuntime(api_key=\"YOUR_API_KEY\")\n273: \n274: response = client.invoke(\n275:     agent_id=\"agent_abc123\",\n276:     message=\"Hello!\"\n277: )\n278: print(response.response)\n279: ```\n280: \n281: ### JavaScript\n282: \n283: ```javascript\n284: import { AgentRuntime } from '@agentcube/sdk';\n285: \n286: const client = new AgentRuntime({ apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY' });\n287: \n288: const response = await client.invoke({\n289:   agentId: 'agent_abc123',\n290:   message: 'Hello!'\n291: });\n292: \n293: console.log(response.response);\n294: ```\n295: \n296: ## Next Steps\n297: \n298: - [Code Interpreter API](/docs/api/code-interpreter)\n299: - [CLI Reference](/docs/api/cli)\n\n(End of file - total 299 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: agent-runtime\ntitle: Agent Runtime API\ndescription: Agent Runtime API reference\nsidebar_position: 1\n---\n\n# Agent Runtime API\n\nThe Agent Runtime API provides programmatic access to agent management and execution.\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttp://localhost:8080/api/v1\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll API requests require an API key in the header:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/agent-runtime.md","time":{"start":1775887268899,"end":1775887268911}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887268915,"sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2137f40011IGpBcV4L3l22n","messageID":"msg_d7b21273a001ZLlD5vTzHHjbRG","sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_ed274d9b4576467f80fc6775","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/code-interpreter.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/code-interpreter.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: code-interpreter\n3: title: Code Interpreter API\n4: description: Code Interpreter API reference\n5: sidebar_position: 2\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Code Interpreter API\n9: \n10: The Code Interpreter provides secure code execution capabilities for agents.\n11: \n12: ## Overview\n13: \n14: The Code Interpreter:\n15: \n16: - Executes code in isolated Docker containers\n17: - Supports multiple languages (Python, JavaScript, Go)\n18: - Captures stdout, stderr, and file outputs\n19: - Enforces resource limits (CPU, memory, time)\n20: \n21: ## Base URL\n22: \n23: ```\n24: http://localhost:8081/api/v1\n25: ```\n26: \n27: ## Endpoints\n28: \n29: ### Execute Code\n30: \n31: Execute code and return the result.\n32: \n33: ```http\n34: POST /execute\n35: ```\n36: \n37: **Request Body:**\n38: \n39: ```json\n40: {\n41:   \"language\": \"python\",\n42:   \"code\": \"print('Hello, World!')\",\n43:   \"timeout\": 30,\n44:   \"memory_limit\": \"512MB\"\n45: }\n46: ```\n47: \n48: **Response:**\n49: \n50: ```json\n51: {\n52:   \"output\": \"Hello, World!\\n\",\n53:   \"error\": \"\",\n54:   \"exit_code\": 0,\n55:   \"execution_time_ms\": 45\n56: }\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ### Execute with Files\n60: \n61: Execute code with input files.\n62: \n63: ```http\n64: POST /execute\n65: ```\n66: \n67: **Request Body:**\n68: \n69: ```json\n70: {\n71:   \"language\": \"python\",\n72:   \"code\": \"import pandas as pd\\ndf = pd.read_csv('data.csv')\\nprint(df.head())\",\n73:   \"files\": {\n74:     \"data.csv\": \"name,value\\na,1\\nb,2\"\n75:   }\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: \n79: **Response:**\n80: \n81: ```json\n82: {\n83:   \"output\": \"   name  value\\n0     a      1\\n1     b      2\\n\",\n84:   \"files\": {},\n85:   \"exit_code\": 0,\n86:   \"execution_time_ms\": 120\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Get Supported Languages\n91: \n92: List supported programming languages.\n93: \n94: ```http\n95: GET /languages\n96: ```\n97: \n98: **Response:**\n99: \n100: ```json\n101: {\n102:   \"languages\": [\n103:     {\n104:       \"id\": \"python\",\n105:       \"name\": \"Python\",\n106:       \"version\": \"3.11\",\n107:       \"extensions\": [\".py\"]\n108:     },\n109:     {\n110:       \"id\": \"javascript\",\n111:       \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n112:       \"version\": \"20\",\n113:       \"extensions\": [\".js\", \".mjs\"]\n114:     },\n115:     {\n116:       \"id\": \"go\",\n117:       \"name\": \"Go\",\n118:       \"version\": \"1.21\",\n119:       \"extensions\": [\".go\"]\n120:     }\n121:   ]\n122: }\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ### Get Execution Status\n126: \n127: Get the status of a previous execution.\n128: \n129: ```http\n130: GET /executions/{execution_id}\n131: ```\n132: \n133: **Response:**\n134: \n135: ```json\n136: {\n137:   \"id\": \"exec_abc123\",\n138:   \"status\": \"completed\",\n139:   \"output\": \"Hello, World!\\n\",\n140:   \"error\": \"\",\n141:   \"exit_code\": 0,\n142:   \"execution_time_ms\": 45,\n143:   \"created_at\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\"\n144: }\n145: ```\n146: \n147: ## Language-Specific Examples\n148: \n149: ### Python\n150: \n151: ```python\n152: import json\n153: \n154: # Parse JSON\n155: data = json.loads('{\"key\": \"value\"}')\n156: print(data)\n157: \n158: # Math operations\n159: import math\n160: result = math.sqrt(16)\n161: print(f\"Square root: {result}\")\n162: \n163: # List processing\n164: numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n165: squared = [n ** 2 for n in numbers]\n166: print(squared)\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ### JavaScript\n170: \n171: ```javascript\n172: // Async operations\n173: const fetchData = async () => {\n174:   const data = await Promise.resolve({ key: 'value' });\n175:   console.log(data);\n176: };\n177: \n178: fetchData();\n179: \n180: // Array methods\n181: const numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];\n182: const doubled = numbers.map(n => n * 2);\n183: console.log(doubled);\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ### Go\n187: \n188: ```go\n189: package main\n190: \n191: import \"fmt\"\n192: \n193: func main() {\n194:     // String formatting\n195:     name := \"World\"\n196:     fmt.Printf(\"Hello, %s!\\n\", name)\n197: \n198:     // Slice operations\n199:     numbers := []int{1, 2, 3, 4, 5}\n200:     sum := 0\n201:     for _, n := range numbers {\n202:         sum += n\n203:     }\n204:     fmt.Printf(\"Sum: %d\\n\", sum)\n205: }\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ## Request Types\n209: \n210: ### ExecuteRequest\n211: \n212: ```typescript\n213: interface ExecuteRequest {\n214:   language: 'python' | 'javascript' | 'go';\n215:   code: string;\n216:   timeout?: number;           // seconds\n217:   memory_limit?: string;     // e.g., \"512MB\"\n218:   cpu_limit?: number;        // number of CPUs\n219:   files?: Record<string, string>;\n220:   environment?: Record<string, string>;\n221: }\n222: ```\n223: \n224: ### ExecuteResponse\n225: \n226: ```typescript\n227: interface ExecuteResponse {\n228:   output: string;\n229:   error: string;\n230:   exit_code: number;\n231:   execution_time_ms: number;\n232:   files?: Record<string, string>;\n233:   logs?: string[];\n234: }\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ## Error Handling\n238: \n239: | Code | Description |\n240: |------|-------------|\n241: | `400` | Invalid request (syntax error) |\n242: | `403` | Code blocked (security) |\n243: | `408` | Execution timeout |\n244: | `413` | Output too large |\n245: | `429` | Rate limited |\n246: | `500` | Internal error |\n247: \n248: ## Security\n249: \n250: ### Allowed Modules (Python)\n251: \n252: By default, the following modules are available:\n253: \n254: - `json`, `math`, `random`, `re`, `datetime`\n255: - `collections`, `itertools`, `functools`\n256: - `pandas`, `numpy` (if configured)\n257: \n258: ### Blocked Operations\n259: \n260: The following are blocked:\n261: \n262: - Network requests\n263: - File system access (except provided files)\n264: - Subprocess execution\n265: - Import of unsafe modules\n266: \n267: ## Webhooks\n268: \n269: Configure webhooks for execution events:\n270: \n271: ```json\n272: {\n273:   \"webhook\": {\n274:     \"url\": \"https://your-server.com/webhook\",\n275:     \"events\": [\"start\", \"complete\", \"error\"]\n276:   }\n277: }\n278: ```\n279: \n280: ## Best Practices\n281: \n282: 1. **Set appropriate timeouts** - 30s for quick tasks, up to 300s for complex operations\n283: 2. **Use memory limits** - 512MB is sufficient for most tasks\n284: 3. **Provide input files** - Use files parameter instead of embedding large data\n285: 4. **Handle errors** - Check exit_code and error fields\n286: \n287: ## Next Steps\n288: \n289: - [Agent Runtime API](/docs/api/agent-runtime)\n290: - [CLI Reference](/docs/api/cli)\n\n(End of file - total 290 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: code-interpreter\ntitle: Code Interpreter API\ndescription: Code Interpreter API reference\nsidebar_position: 2\n---\n\n# Code Interpreter API\n\nThe Code Interpreter provides secure code execution capabilities for agents.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Code Interpreter:\n\n- Executes code in isolated Docker containers\n- Supports multiple languages (Python, JavaScript, Go)\n- Captures stdout, stderr, and file outputs\n- Enforces resource limits (CPU, memory, time)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/docs/docs/api/code-interpreter.md","time":{"start":1775887268902,"end":1775887268913}}}}
