{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887345116,"sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2261cf001qkdCOEaRdegoXl","messageID":"msg_d7b2256280013fO43S147kYAP0","sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_c2f42cdd00994818a960863e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-042 — Docusaurus Documentation Site Framework\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture Overview\n4: \n5: The AgentCube documentation site is a Docusaurus-based static documentation platform with the following architectural layers:\n6: \n7: - **Build Layer**: Docusaurus CLI and build system (Node.js/TypeScript)\n8: - **Content Layer**: Markdown/MDX documentation files organized by category\n9: - **Presentation Layer**: Docusaurus React theme components\n10: - **Deployment Layer**: Static site generation output for hosting\n11: \n12: ## 2. Module Structure\n13: \n14: ```\n15: docs/\n16: ├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus configuration (Config interface)\n17: ├── sidebars.ts                    # Sidebar navigation (SidebarsConfig)\n18: ├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript configuration\n19: ├── package.json                   # Node dependencies and scripts\n20: ├── package-lock.json\n21: ├── static/                        # Static assets\n22: │   ├── img/\n23: │   │   ├── logo.svg\n24: │   │   ├── favicon.ico\n25: │   │   └── social-card.png\n26: │   └── robots.txt\n27: ├── docs/                          # Documentation source files\n28: │   ├── index.md                   # Landing page\n29: │   ├── getting-started/\n30: │   │   ├── installation.md\n31: │   │   └── quickstart.md\n32: │   ├── guides/\n33: │   │   ├── architecture.md\n34: │   │   ├── configuration.md\n35: │   │   └── monitoring.md\n36: │   ├── api/\n37: │   │   ├── agent-runtime.md\n38: │   │   ├── code-interpreter.md\n39: │   │   └── cli.md\n40: │   └── contributed/\n41: │       ├── overview.md\n42: │       ├── development.md\n43: │       └── coding-standards.md\n44: ├── blog/                          # Blog posts (optional)\n45: ├── src/\n46: │   ├── css/\n47: │   │   └── custom.css            # Custom theme overrides\n48: │   ├── pages/\n49: │   │   ├── index.tsx             # Custom landing page\n50: │   │   └── index.module.css\n51: │   └── theme/\n52: │       └── Footer                # Custom footer component\n53: ├── versioned_docs/                # Versioned documentation\n54: │   └── version-1.0.0/\n55: ├── versioned_sidebars/            # Sidebars for versions\n56: ├── versioned_blog/                # Versioned blog posts\n57: └── scripts/\n58:     └── build.sh                  # Build script\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ## 3. Data Structures\n62: \n63: ### 3.1 Docusaurus Configuration\n64: \n65: ```typescript\n66: // docusaurus.config.ts types (from @docusaurus/types)\n67: \n68: interface Config {\n69:   title: string;\n70:   tagline?: string;\n71:   url: string;\n72:   baseUrl: string;\n73:   onBrokenLinks?: 'throw' | 'warn' | 'ignore';\n74:   onBrokenMarkdownLinks?: 'throw' | 'warn' | 'ignore';\n75:   favicon?: string;\n76:   organizationName?: string;\n77:   projectName?: string;\n78:   presets?: Preset[];\n79:   themeConfig?: ThemeConfig;\n80:   plugins?: Plugin[];\n81:   themes?: Theme[];\n82:   markdown?: MarkdownConfig;\n83: }\n84: \n85: interface ThemeConfig {\n86:   image?: string;\n87:   navbar?: Navbar;\n88:   footer?: Footer;\n89:   prism?: PrismThemeConfig;\n90:   announcementBar?: AnnouncementBar;\n91:   colorMode?: ColorModeConfig;\n92:   docs?: DocsThemeConfig;\n93:   tableOfContents?: TableOfContentsConfig;\n94: }\n95: \n96: interface Navbar {\n97:   title?: string;\n98:   logo?: {\n99:     src: string;\n100:     alt?: string;\n101:     href?: string;\n102:   };\n103:   items: NavbarItem[];\n104:   hideOnScroll?: boolean;\n105: }\n106: \n107: type NavbarItem = \n108:   | { type: 'doc'; docId: string; label: string; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n109:   | { type: 'docSidebar'; sidebarId: string; label: string; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n110:   | { type: 'docsVersionDropdown'; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n111:   | { type: 'localeDropdown'; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n112:   | { type: 'search' }\n113:   | { type: 'href'; href: string; label: string; position: 'left' | 'right' }\n114:   | { type: 'html'; html: string; position: 'left' | 'right' };\n115: \n116: interface Footer {\n117:   style: 'light' | 'dark';\n118:   links?: FooterLink[];\n119:   copyright?: string;\n120:   logo?: {\n121:     src: string;\n122:     alt?: string;\n123:     href?: string;\n124:   };\n125: }\n126: \n127: interface FooterLink {\n128:   title?: string;\n129:   items: FooterItem[];\n130: }\n131: \n132: interface FooterItem {\n133:   label: string;\n134:   href?: string;\n135:   to?: string;\n136:   docId?: string;\n137: }\n138: ```\n139: \n140: ### 3.2 Sidebar Configuration\n141: \n142: ```typescript\n143: // sidebars.ts types (from @docusaurus/plugin-content-docs)\n144: \n145: interface SidebarsConfig {\n146:   [sidebarId: string]: SidebarItem[];\n147: }\n148: \n149: type SidebarItem = \n150:   | string  // Document ID\n151:   | {\n152:       type: 'category';\n153:       label: string;\n154:       items: SidebarItem[];\n155:       collapsed?: boolean;\n156:       collapsible?: boolean;\n157:       className?: string;\n158:     }\n159:   | {\n160:       type: 'autogenerated';\n161:       dirName: string;\n162:     }\n163:   | {\n164:       type: 'link';\n165:       label: string;\n166:       href: string;\n167:     }\n168:   | {\n169:       type: 'ref';\n170:       id: string;\n171:     };\n172: ```\n173: \n174: ### 3.3 Document Frontmatter\n175: \n176: ```typescript\n177: // Standard frontmatter for docs\n178: \n179: interface DocFrontmatter {\n180:   id?: string;\n181:   title: string;\n182:   description?: string;\n183:   sidebar_label?: string;\n184:   sidebar_position?: number;\n185:   hide_title?: boolean;\n186:   hide_table_of_contents?: boolean;\n187:   tags?: string[];\n188:   image?: string;\n189:   keywords?: string[];\n190:   draft?: boolean;\n191:   slug?: string;\n192: }\n193: ```\n194: \n195: ## 4. API Contracts\n196: \n197: ### 4.1 Docusaurus CLI Commands\n198: \n199: | Command | Description | Output |\n200: |---------|-------------|--------|\n201: | `npm run start` | Start dev server (hot reload) | `http://localhost:3000` |\n202: | `npm run build` | Build static site | `build/` directory |\n203: | `npm run deploy` | Deploy to GitHub Pages | GitHub Pages |\n204: | `npm run serve` | Serve built site locally | `http://localhost:3000` |\n205: | `npm run clear` | Clear Docusaurus cache | Removes `.docusaurus/` |\n206: | `docusaurus write-translations` | Generate translation files | `i18n/` directory |\n207: | `docusaurus write-heading-ids` | Generate heading IDs | Updates MD files |\n208: \n209: ### 4.2 Build Output Structure\n210: \n211: ```\n212: build/\n213: ├── index.html                    # Landing page\n214: ├── docs/\n215: │   ├── intro/index.html\n216: │   ├── getting-started/\n217: │   │   ├── installation/index.html\n218: │   │   └── quickstart/index.html\n219: │   └── ...\n220: ├── blog/\n221: │   └── index.html\n222: ├── img/\n223: │   ├── logo.svg\n224: │   └── favicon.ico\n225: ├── css/\n226: │   └── styles.css\n227: ├── js/\n228: │   └── main.js\n229: └── 404.html                      # Not found page\n230: ```\n231: \n232: ### 4.3 Environment Variables\n233: \n234: | Variable | Description | Default |\n235: |----------|-------------|---------|\n236: | `NODE_ENV` | Build environment | `development` |\n237: | `GIT_USER` | GitHub username for deployment | — |\n238: | `USE_SSH` | Use SSH for GitHub deploy | `false` |\n239: \n240: ## 5. Error Handling\n241: \n242: ### 5.1 Build-Time Errors\n243: \n244: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n245: |-------|-------|------------|\n246: | `Error: Docusaurus node version mismatch` | Node.js version incompatible | Use Node.js 18+ |\n247: | `Error: Broken link detected` | Invalid internal link | Fix link in MD file |\n248: | `Error: Build failed due to parsing errors` | Invalid MDX/React syntax | Check MDX content |\n249: | `Error: Module not found` | Missing dependency | Run `npm install` |\n250: \n251: ### 5.2 Validation During Build\n252: \n253: Docusaurus performs automatic validation:\n254: \n255: 1. **Link Validation**: `onBrokenLinks` config option\n256:    - `'throw'`: Fail build on broken links\n257:    - `'warn'`: Log warning, continue build\n258:    - `'ignore'`: Skip validation\n259: \n260: 2. **Markdown Validation**: `onBrokenMarkdownLinks` config option\n261: \n262: 3. **TypeScript Validation**: Via `tsc` during build\n263: \n264: ### 5.3 Common Issues\n265: \n266: | Issue | Solution |\n267: |-------|----------|\n268: | Slow hot reload | Run `npm run clear` |\n269: | Stale content | Clear browser cache or disable SWC cache |\n270: | CSS not applying | Check `custom.css` syntax |\n271: | Sidebar not showing | Verify `sidebars.ts` structure |\n272: | Version dropdown missing | Add version with `npm run docusaurus docs:version` |\n273: \n274: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n275: \n276: ### 6.1 Test Framework\n277: \n278: | Tool | Purpose |\n279: |------|---------|\n280: | `npm run build` | Validate build process |\n281: | `npm run start` | Validate dev server |\n282: | `eslint` | Lint TypeScript and React |\n283: | `prettier` | Format check for MD/MDX |\n284: \n285: ### 6.2 Validation Tests\n286: \n287: | Test | Command | Success Criteria |\n288: |------|---------|------------------|\n289: | Build | `npm run build` | Exit code 0, `build/` exists |\n290: | Dev server | `npm run start` | Server starts without errors |\n291: | Link check | Build with `onBrokenLinks: 'throw'` | No broken link errors |\n292: | Type check | `npx tsc --noEmit` | No TypeScript errors |\n293: | Lint | `npx eslint .` | No lint errors |\n294: | Format | `npx prettier --check .` | No format violations |\n295: \n296: ### 6.3 Content Validation\n297: \n298: | Check | Implementation |\n299: |-------|----------------|\n300: | Frontmatter completeness | Required fields: `title` |\n301: | Code block syntax | Prism highlighting validation |\n302: | Image references | File existence check |\n303: | Internal links | Docusaurus link validation |\n304: | Heading hierarchy | MDX linting rules |\n305: \n306: ### 6.4 Browser Testing\n307: \n308: | Environment | Target |\n309: |-------------|--------|\n310: | Chrome/Edge | Latest |\n311: | Firefox | Latest |\n312: | Safari | Latest |\n313: | Mobile viewport | 375px width |\n314: \n315: ### 6.5 CI Integration\n316: \n317: ```yaml\n318: # .github/workflows/docs.yml\n319: name: Documentation\n320: \n321: on:\n322:   push:\n323:     branches: [main]\n324:     paths: ['docs/**']\n325: \n326: jobs:\n327:   build:\n328:     runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n329:     steps:\n330:       - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n331:       - uses: actions/setup-node@v4\n332:         with:\n333:           node-version: '18'\n334:       - run: npm ci\n335:       - run: npm run build\n336:       - run: npm run lint\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ## 7. Dependencies\n340: \n341: ### 7.1 Core Dependencies\n342: \n343: ```json\n344: {\n345:   \"dependencies\": {\n346:     \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.7.0\",\n347:     \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.7.0\",\n348:     \"@docusaurus/theme-classic\": \"^3.7.0\",\n349:     \"@docusaurus/theme-common\": \"^3.7.0\",\n350:     \"@mdx-js/react\": \"^3.0.0\",\n351:     \"clsx\": \"^2.1.0\",\n352:     \"prism-react-renderer\": \"^2.3.0\",\n353:     \"react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n354:     \"react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\"\n355:   }\n356: }\n357: ```\n358: \n359: ### 7.2 Dev Dependencies\n360: \n361: ```json\n362: {\n363:   \"devDependencies\": {\n364:     \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.7.0\",\n365:     \"@types/react\": \"^18.2.0\",\n366:     \"@types/react-dom\": \"^18.2.0\",\n367:     \"eslint\": \"^8.57.0\",\n368:     \"prettier\": \"^3.2.0\",\n369:     \"typescript\": \"^5.3.0\"\n370:   }\n371: }\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ## 8. Configuration Summary\n375: \n376: | Configuration File | Purpose |\n377: |--------------------|---------|\n378: | `docusaurus.config.ts` | Site metadata, presets, theme config |\n379: | `sidebars.ts` | Navigation structure |\n380: | `tsconfig.json` | TypeScript options |\n381: | `src/css/custom.css` | Theme customization |\n382: | `.eslintrc.js` | Linting rules |\n383: | `.prettierrc` | Code formatting |\n384: \n385: ## 9. Acceptance Criteria\n386: \n387: | Requirement | Verification |\n388: |-------------|--------------|\n389: | Dev server starts | `npm run start` succeeds |\n390: | Static build succeeds | `npm run build` produces `build/` |\n391: | All docs render | Manual browser check |\n392: | Navigation works | Click all sidebar items |\n393: | Version dropdown | At least one version exists |\n394: | Responsive design | Test mobile viewport |\n395: | 404 page works | Navigate to invalid URL |\n396: | No console errors | Check browser DevTools |\n\n(End of file - total 396 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-042 — Docusaurus Documentation Site Framework\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\nThe AgentCube documentation site is a Docusaurus-based static documentation platform with the following architectural layers:\n\n- **Build Layer**: Docusaurus CLI and build system (Node.js/TypeScript)\n- **Content Layer**: Markdown/MDX documentation files organized by category\n- **Presentation Layer**: Docusaurus React theme components\n- **Deployment Layer**: Static site generation output for hosting\n\n## 2. Module Structure\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── docusaurus.config.ts          # Docusaurus configuration (Config interface)\n├── sidebars.ts                    # Sidebar navigation (SidebarsConfig)\n├── tsconfig.json                  # TypeScript configuration\n├── package.json                   # Node dependencies and scripts\n├── package-lock.json","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775887345098,"end":1775887345113}}}}
