{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775887347736,"sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b227017001enlLwwuRSd5l8B","messageID":"msg_d7b2266170014JBdmZWKikIdAY","sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887410821,"sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","part":{"id":"prt_d7b227619001hH2cnP0MWO0CWa","messageID":"msg_d7b2266170014JBdmZWKikIdAY","sessionID":"ses_284df9b52ffe1wc49UbpN6zfYj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_990b6109cc5e43958adddc50","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-043 — Architecture Design Document & API Documentation\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document specifies the technical implementation for creating comprehensive architecture design documentation and API documentation for the AgentCube project. The documentation will be rendered using Docusaurus and will serve as the single source of truth for developers integrating with AgentCube.\n\n## 1. System Architecture\n\n### 1.1 High-Level Component Diagram\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TB\n    subgraph Client[\"Client Layer\"]\n        SDK[Python SDK]\n        CLI[CLI Tool]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph Control[\"Control Plane\"]\n        CP[Control Plane]\n        WM[Workload Manager]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph Data[\"Data Plane\"]\n        Router[Router Service]\n        AgentRuntime[Agent Runtime]\n        CodeInt[Code Interpreter]\n    end\n    \n    subgraph Infra[\"Infrastructure\"]\n        K8s[Kubernetes]\n        Docker[Docker]\n    end\n    \n    SDK --> CP\n    CLI --> CP\n    CP --> WM\n    SDK --> Router\n    Router --> AgentRuntime\n    Router --> CodeInt\n    AgentRuntime --> K8s\n    CodeInt --> Docker\n```\n\n### 1.2 Core Components\n\n| Component | Responsibility | Location |\n|-----------|----------------|----------|\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | SDK client for agent invocation | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | SDK client for code execution | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` |\n| `PackRuntime` | Workspace packing orchestration | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` |\n| `BuildRuntime` | Docker image building | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` |\n| `PublishRuntime` | Agent deployment | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` |\n| `InvokeRuntime` | Agent invocation | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` |\n| `StatusRuntime` | Status checking | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` |\n| `MetadataService` | Metadata management | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` |\n| `DockerService` | Docker operations | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` |\n| `KubernetesProvider` | K8s deployments | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | Session management | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | Agent communication | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Code execution | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` |\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 AgentMetadata Model\n\n```python\nclass AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n    agent_name: str                           # Unique identifier\n    description: Optional[str]                # Human-readable summary\n    language: str                             # \"python\" or \"java\"\n    entrypoint: str                           # Launch command\n    port: int                                 # Exposed port (1-65535)\n    build_mode: str                           # \"local\" or \"cloud\"\n    version: Optional[str]                    # Semantic version\n    image: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]           # Container image info\n    requirements_file: Optional[str]         # Dependencies file\n    registry_url: Optional[str]              # Image registry\n    agent_endpoint: Optional[str]            # Runtime endpoint\n    workload_manager_url: Optional[str]      # WM service URL\n    router_url: Optional[str]                # Router URL\n    agent_id: Optional[str]                  # Deployed agent ID\n    session_id: Optional[str]                # Active session ID\n```\n\n### 2.2 Runtime Operation Results\n\n| Operation | Return Type | Key Fields |\n|-----------|-------------|------------|\n| `PackRuntime.pack()` | `dict` | `agent_name`, `workspace_path`, `output_path`, `metadata_file`, `dockerfile_generated` |\n| `BuildRuntime.build()` | `dict` | `agent_name`, `image_name`, `image_tag`, `image_id`, `version` |\n| `PublishRuntime.publish()` | `dict` | `agent_name`, `provider`, `endpoint`, `status` |\n| `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` | `dict` | `agent_name`, `payload`, `response` |\n| `StatusRuntime.get_status()` | `dict` | `agent_name`, `agent_id`, `provider`, `status`, `endpoint`, `namespace` |\n\n### 2.3 Client Initialization Parameters\n\n**AgentRuntimeClient:**\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str = \"my-agent\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = DEFAULT_TIMEOUT,\n        connect_timeout: float = DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT,\n        pool_connections: int = DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS,\n        pool_maxsize: int = DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE,\n    )\n```\n\n**CodeInterpreterClient:**\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n        session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    )\n```\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 SDK Client API\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient Methods\n\n| Method | Signature | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `__init__` | `(self, **kwargs)` | Initialize client with configuration |\n| `_bootstrap_session` | `(self) -> str` | Create new session via Router |\n| `invoke` | `(self, payload: dict, timeout=None) -> dict` | Invoke agent with payload |\n| `close` | `(self) -> None` | Release resources |\n| `session_id` | `property` | Current session ID |\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient Methods\n\n| Method | Signature | Description |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `__init__` | `(self, **kwargs)` | Initialize client |\n| `_create_session` | `(self) -> str` | Create session via Control Plane |\n| `execute_command` | `(self, command: str, timeout=None) -> Dict` | Execute shell command |\n| `run_code` | `(self, code: str, language=\"python\", timeout=None) -> Dict` | Run code in sandbox |\n| `write_file` | `(self, content: str, remote_path: str, mode=\"0644\") -> Dict` | Write file to sandbox |\n| `upload_file` | `(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> Dict` | Upload local file |\n| `download_file` | `(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None` | Download file from sandbox |\n| `list_files` | `(self, path=\".\") -> Dict` | List sandbox files |\n| `stop` | `(self) -> None` | Stop session and cleanup |\n| `session_id` | `property` | Current session ID |\n\n### 3.2 Runtime Operation API\n\n#### PackRuntime\n\n```python\nclass PackRuntime:\n    def pack(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: str,\n        agent_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        language: Optional[str] = None,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        port: Optional[int] = None,\n        build_mode: Optional[str] = None,\n        description: Optional[str] = None,\n        requirements_file: Optional[str] = None,\n        output: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n    ) -> dict\n```\n\n#### BuildRuntime\n\n```python\nclass BuildRuntime:\n    def build(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: str,\n        proxy: Optional[str] = None,\n        cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None,\n        output: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n    ) -> dict\n```\n\n#### PublishRuntime\n\n```python\nclass PublishRuntime:\n    def publish(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: str,\n        version: Optional[str] = None,\n        image_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        image_username: Optional[str] = None,\n        image_password: Optional[str] = None,\n        description: Optional[str] = None,\n        region: Optional[str] = None,\n        cloud_provider: Optional[str] = None,\n        provider: str = \"agentcube\",\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        replicas: Optional[int] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        verbose: bool = False,\n    ) -> dict\n```\n\n#### InvokeRuntime\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: str,\n        payload: str = \"{}\",\n        header_list: Optional[list[str]] = None,\n        provider: str = \"agentcube\",\n        verbose: bool = False,\n    ) -> dict\n```\n\n#### StatusRuntime\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def get_status(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: str,\n        provider: str = \"agentcube\",\n    ) -> dict\n```\n\n### 3.3 CLI Commands\n\n| Command | Usage | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| `pack` | `kubectl-agentcube pack [-f WORKSPACE] [--agent-name NAME] [--language LANG] [--entrypoint CMD] [--port PORT] [--build-mode MODE] [--description DESC] [--output PATH] [-v]` | Pack agent workspace |\n| `build` | `kubectl-agentcube build [-f WORKSPACE] [-p PROXY] [--cloud-provider PROVIDER] [--output PATH] [-v]` | Build Docker image |\n| `publish` | `kubectl-agentcube publish [-f WORKSPACE] [--version VERSION] [--image-url URL] [--image-username USER] [--image-password PASS] [--description DESC] [--region REGION] [--provider PROVIDER] [--node-port PORT] [--replicas N] [--namespace NS] [-v]` | Deploy agent |\n| `invoke` | `kubectl-agentcube invoke [-f WORKSPACE] [--payload JSON] [--header KEY:VALUE] [--provider PROVIDER] [-v]` | Invoke published agent |\n| `status` | `kubectl-agentcube status [-f WORKSPACE] [--provider PROVIDER] [-v]` | Check agent status |\n| `version` | `kubectl-agentcube version` | Show version |\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Exception Hierarchy\n\n```\nAgentCubeError (base)\n├── CommandExecutionError\n│   ├── exit_code: Optional[int]\n│   ├── stderr: Optional[str]\n│   └── command: Optional[str]\n├── SessionError\n└── DataPlaneError\n```\n\n### 4.2 Exception Specifications\n\n| Exception | Raised When | Properties |\n|-----------|-------------|------------|\n| `AgentCubeError` | Base exception for all SDK errors | `message` |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Command returns non-zero exit code | `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command` |\n| `SessionError` | Session bootstrap or management fails | `message` |\n| `DataPlaneError` | Data plane communication fails | `message` |\n| `ValueError` | Invalid input parameters | Standard Python |\n| `FileNotFoundError` | Workspace or metadata not found | Standard Python |\n\n### 4.3 Error Response Patterns\n\nSDK operations return error information in responses:\n\n```python\n# HTTP error handling\nresponse.raise_for_status()  # Raises requests.HTTPError\n\n# Session errors\nif not session_id:\n    raise SessionError(\"Session bootstrap failed: {detail}\")\n\n# Command execution errors\nif exit_code != 0:\n    raise CommandExecutionError(\n        f\"Command failed with exit code {exit_code}\",\n        exit_code=exit_code,\n        stderr=stderr,\n        command=command,\n    )\n```\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Test Structure\n\n```\ntests/\n├── conftest.py                    # Shared fixtures\n├── test_agent_runtime_client.py   # AgentRuntimeClient tests\n├── test_code_interpreter.py       # CodeInterpreterClient tests\n├── test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\n├── test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n├── test_control_plane.py\n├── test_docker_service.py\n├── test_metadata_service.py\n├── test_k8s_provider.py\n├── test_pack_runtime.py\n├── test_build_runtime.py\n├── test_publish_runtime.py\n├── test_invoke_runtime.py\n├── test_status_runtime.py\n├── test_exceptions.py\n├── test_utils.py\n└── test_http.py\n```\n\n### 5.2 Test Coverage Areas\n\n| Component | Test Focus |\n|-----------|------------|\n| `AgentRuntimeClient` | Session bootstrapping, invocation, resource cleanup |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | Session lifecycle, command execution, file operations |\n| `PackRuntime` | Workspace validation, metadata handling, Dockerfile generation |\n| `BuildRuntime` | Version incrementing, Docker build, error recovery |\n| `PublishRuntime` | K8s/AgentCube provider deployment |\n| `MetadataService` | Load/save/validate metadata files |\n| `DockerService` | Dockerfile generation, image building |\n\n### 5.3 Test Fixtures\n\nKey fixtures in `conftest.py`:\n\n| Fixture | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `temp_workspace` | Create temporary workspace directory |\n| `sample_metadata` | Provide sample AgentMetadata |\n| `mock_docker` | Mock Docker client |\n| `mock_k8s` | Mock Kubernetes client |\n| `router_url` | Test Router endpoint |\n\n### 5.4 Running Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests\npytest\n\n# Run with coverage\npytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=html\n\n# Run specific test file\npytest tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py\n\n# Run with verbose output\npytest -v\n\n# Run tests matching pattern\npytest -k \"test_pack\"\n```\n\n## 6. Documentation Structure\n\n### 6.1 Architecture Documentation\n\n| Document | Content |\n|----------|---------|\n| `docs/docs/architecture/system-design.md` | System-level component diagram, interactions |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/client-sdk.md` | SDK client architecture details |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/services.md` | Service layer architecture |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/runtime.md` | Runtime operations workflow |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md` | Data flow and sequence diagrams |\n\n### 6.2 API Documentation\n\n| Document | Content |\n|----------|---------|\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-agent-runtime.md` | AgentRuntimeClient API reference |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-code-interpreter.md` | CodeInterpreterClient API reference |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-services.md` | Service layer API reference |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-runtime.md` | Runtime operations API reference |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-exceptions.md` | Exception reference |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-cli.md` | CLI command reference |\n\n### 6.3 Documentation Format\n\nEach API document follows this structure:\n\n```markdown\n# Component Name\n\n## Overview\nBrief description of the component's purpose.\n\n## Constructor\n```python\nClassName(param1: str, param2: int = 10)\n```\n\n## Parameters\n| Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| param1 | str | Required | Description |\n\n## Methods\n\n### method_name\n\n```python\nclient.method_name(arg1: str) -> dict\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `arg1` (str): Description\n\n**Returns:** `dict` - Description\n\n**Raises:** `ExceptionType` - When condition\n\n**Example:**\n```python\nresult = client.method_name(\"value\")\n```\n\n## Error Handling\nDescription of error handling patterns.\n```\n\n## 7. Implementation Notes\n\n### 7.1 Key Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `requests` | ^2.31.0 | HTTP client |\n| `pydantic` | ^2.5.0 | Data validation |\n| `pyyaml` | ^6.0 | YAML parsing |\n| `packaging` | ^24.0 | Version parsing |\n| `typer` | ^0.12.0 | CLI framework |\n| `rich` | ^13.7.0 | Terminal output |\n\n### 7.2 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Used By | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | All clients | Router service URL |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | CodeInterpreterClient | Workload Manager URL |\n| `HTTP_PROXY` | BuildRuntime | Proxy for builds |\n\n### 7.3 Default Values\n\n| Parameter | Default |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | 120 seconds |\n| `DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT` | 5.0 seconds |\n| `DEFAULT_POOL_CONNECTIONS` | 10 |\n| `DEFAULT_POOL_MAXSIZE` | 10 |\n| `DEFAULT_TTL` | 3600 seconds |\n| `DEFAULT_PORT` | 8080 |\n\n## 8. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Architecture diagrams render correctly in Docusaurus\n- [ ] All SDK client methods documented with parameters and return types\n- [ ] All runtime operations documented with CLI equivalents\n- [ ] Exception hierarchy documented with usage examples\n- [ ] Testing strategy documented with coverage goals\n- [ ] Code examples are tested and verified to work\n- [ ] Cross-references between related documents functional\n\n## 9. References\n\n- Docusaurus Documentation: https://docusaurus.io/\n- Mermaid Diagrams: https://mermaid.js.org/\n- Pydantic Models: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n- Typer CLI: https://typer.tiangolo.com/","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/agent_runtime.py\">\nERROR [147:62] Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to declared type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n  Type \"int | tuple[float, float] | None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n    Type \"None\" is not assignable to type \"int | tuple[float, float]\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"int\"\n      \"None\" is not assignable to \"tuple[float, float]\"\nERROR [153:31] \"invoke\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [153:16] Argument missing for parameter \"payload\"\nERROR [171:33] Cannot assign to attribute \"_session\" for class \"AgentRuntimeClient*\"\n  \"None\" is not assignable to \"Session\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [97:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [100:28] Argument of type \"st